Lungile Tom was known to many as the bubbly eNCA camera operator. Courtesy #DStv403 CAPE TOWN - He was known to many as the bubbly eNCA camera operator, but Lungile Tom was also his mother's only child, a husband, a dad and a friend. From 25-29 November government is asking South Africans to remember those who lost their lives to COVID-19 and we, as eNCA, are remembering our beloved colleague. WATCH: Tribute to eNCA cameraman Lungile Tom Tom may be a statistic of this devastating virus, but his memory lives on. As a fitting tribute, he was named a winner in the Vodacom Regional Journalism Awards earlier this month. eNCA’s Nobesuthu Hejana spoke to his family. Watch the video above.